.TH SVGFONT 1 "2026" "svgfont" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
svgfont \- Extract and add glyphs to SVG font files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B svgfont
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fB\-u\fR \fISVGFILE\fR
.br
.B svgfont
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fB\-a\fR \fIFONTSVG\fR \fISVGFILE\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBsvgfont\fR is a utility for working with SVG font files. It can extract
glyphs from an SVG font file into individual SVG files, or add SVG files as
glyphs to an existing SVG font file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-extract\fR
Extract font glyphs from an SVG font file. The glyphs will be saved as
individual SVG files in an output directory.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-add\fR \fIFONTSVG\fR
Add SVG files as font glyphs to the font SVG file specified by \fIFONTSVG\fR.
The glyph name is derived from the filename (without extension).
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-outdir\fR \fIDIR\fR
Specify the output directory for extracted glyphs. If not specified, the
default is a directory beside the SVG file (e.g., \fIfoo/bar.svg\fR will
extract to \fIfoo/bar/\fR).
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Enable verbose mode, showing debug messages.
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Enable quiet mode, only showing error messages.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
Extract all glyphs from a font file:
.RS
.B svgfont -u materialdesignicons-webfont.svg
.RE
.PP
Extract glyphs to a specific directory:
.RS
.B svgfont -u font.svg -o output/
.RE
.PP
Add SVG files as glyphs to a font file:
.RS
.B svgfont -a font.svg icon1.svg icon2.svg icon3.svg
.RE
.PP
Extract with verbose output:
.RS
.B svgfont -v -u font.svg
.RE
